  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Maria Weston Chapman writes about the progress of the anti-slavery fair in Boston. She asks Elizabeth B. Chapman Laugel to write to Mrs. Louise Keller and tell her that her box of contributions [for the anti-slavery fair] arrived safely. Chapman gives the prices at which the various items at fair were sold. Chapman says that &quot;the population of Boston is one half foreign.&quot; She comments on the Boston Irish.</subfield>
